Exclusion criteria included the following:
Incomplete surgical procedures;
Re-injury of the operated joint during follow-up;
Incomplete or missing clinical data.

Clinical outcomes were assessed using the following validated scores:
The Visual Analog Scale (VAS) for pain;
The Tegner–Lysholm Score (TLS) for knee function;
The Knee Society Score (KSS) for functional assessment;
The Modified Cincinnati Score (MCS) for patient-reported knee function.
